{"info": {"author": "shaneing", "author_email": "z.shane.ing@gamil.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Operating System :: MacOS", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: Unix", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "description": "# Python Viper\n\nThis project was inspired by [spf13/viper](https://github.com/spf13/viper).\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install py-viper\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nimport tempfile\nimport viper\n\nyaml_example = b'''\nhello:\n  name: foo\n'''\n\n\nclass Hello:\n    name = ''\n\n\nclass Config:\n    hello = Hello\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix='.yaml') as temp:\n        temp.write(yaml_example)\n        temp.seek(0)\n        viper.set_config_path(temp.name)\n        viper.read_config()\n        assert viper.get('hello.name') == 'foo'\n\n        conf = Config()\n        viper.unmarshal(conf)\n        assert conf.hello.name == 'foo'\n```\n\nYou can also use remote config instead of local config:\n\n```python\nviper.set_config_type('yml')\nviper.set_remote_provider('consul', '127.0.0.1', 8500, 'hello')\nviper.read_remote_config()\n```\n\nNote:\n\n- The config type only supports *yaml* or *yml*.\n- The backend of remote config only supports *consul*.\n\n## TODO\n\n- [x] Read remote config\n- [x] Unmarshal config\n- [x] Add support for JSON", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/shaneing/python-viper", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "py-viper", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-viper/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-viper/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/shaneing/python-viper"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-viper/0.1.0.dev5/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Python viper", "version": "0.1.0.dev5", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Python Viper</h1>\n<p>This project was inspired by <a href=\"https://github.com/spf13/viper\" rel=\"nofollow\">spf13/viper</a>.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre><code>pip install py-viper\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">tempfile</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">viper</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">yaml_example</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s1\">'''</span>\n<span class=\"s1\">hello:</span>\n<span class=\"s1\">  name: foo</span>\n<span class=\"s1\">'''</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">Hello</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">name</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">''</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">Config</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">hello</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Hello</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"vm\">__name__</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s1\">'__main__'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">tempfile</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">NamedTemporaryFile</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">suffix</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'.yaml'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">temp</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">temp</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">yaml_example</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">temp</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">seek</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">viper</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_config_path</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">temp</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">viper</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read_config</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">viper</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'hello.name'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s1\">'foo'</span>\n\n        <span class=\"n\">conf</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Config</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">viper</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">unmarshal</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">conf</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">conf</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">hello</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">name</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s1\">'foo'</span>\n</pre>\n<p>You can also use remote config instead of local config:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">viper</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_config_type</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'yml'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">viper</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_remote_provider</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'consul'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'127.0.0.1'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">8500</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'hello'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">viper</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read_remote_config</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Note:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The config type only supports <em>yaml</em> or <em>yml</em>.</li>\n<li>The backend of remote config only supports <em>consul</em>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>TODO</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[x] Read remote config</li>\n<li>[x] Unmarshal config</li>\n<li>[x] Add support for JSON</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6526570, "releases": {"0.1.0.dev1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "b31fd07182750e41f6ed6d958c98547c", "sha256": "e112871cd8e5115ee8e9158e194c1e51be901db50f1dfe459a5dc26f6e92651b"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "py-viper-0.1.0.dev1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "b31fd07182750e41f6ed6d958c98547c", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3202, "upload_time": "2020-01-13T15:40:47", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-01-13T15:40:47.290522Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/08/83/3740a7753df0e0c211199799c62c7453058e90551d07dcf8c95aa961f635/py-viper-0.1.0.dev1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.0.dev2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "64c0933d0d8ce78adf72cc85174bafd3", "sha256": "9d7e5e9e4ead3e1659344b535e0b6d7eb0af4f1ef7f62d277a889eb8d79fb7f1"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "py-viper-0.1.0.dev2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "64c0933d0d8ce78adf72cc85174bafd3", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3782, "upload_time": "2020-01-15T16:15:06", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-01-15T16:15:06.415101Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/26/c3/3d212a584388c50b260b8aae574db4be889d0b5615f51c0ed5cf85bde044/py-viper-0.1.0.dev2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.0.dev4": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "f7c7ce5fd39d38ec5ae7e59a23be4705", "sha256": "661d23a876e4eefdb1d0e3e25fd0112f7aac0c67cf38bf86a50f1739a27bb65c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "py-viper-0.1.0.dev4.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "f7c7ce5fd3